ho，因此它还可以传输音乐、获取天气信息、控制智能家居设备以及执行其他与 Alexa 相关的任务。虽然没有这样的设备对于注重隐私的人来说是理想的选择，但至少有一个物理相机快门和一个麦克风静音按钮。</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><p>新的 Echo Show 5 稍微改进了处理器和扬声器系统，但它仍然不如<a data-i13n="elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;cpos:8;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiI2NmVhNTY3YS1jOTg3LTRjMmUtYTJmZi0wMjkwNGVmZGU2ZWEiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYW1hem9uLmNvbS9kcC9CMDg0REM0TFc2P3RhZz1nZGd0MGMtcC1vLTFwcC0yMCIsImNvbnRlbnRVdWlkIjoiOTVkZDA5MTItNzkwNy00MmUxLWE2OTMtZGNhMGIwNjNiYjY1In0&amp;signature=AQAAATvby5w7z50_Yuq8H14DMLrWq1u1kWgFMcl7ilblz-Fm&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2Fdp%2FB084DC4LW6" class="rapid-with-clickid">Echo Show 8</a>那样快速或完整，这是我们向那些想要 Alexa 智能显示器的人的主要推荐。 （这款 8 英寸显示屏现在的售价为 75 美元，比 Prime Day 的价格贵了 15 美元。）同样，200 万像素摄像头对于视频通话来说表现平平，而 960 x 480 分辨率的显示屏对于查看照片来说远非豪华。 。不过，如果您经常使用 Alexa，空间有限，并且希望花尽可能少的钱购买功能强大的显示屏，那么 Echo Show 5 在这个价格上还是有意义的。</p><p><em>在 Twitter 上</em><em>关注</em><a data-i13n="cpos:9;pos:1" href="https://twitter.com/EngadgetDeals"><em>@EngadgetDeals</em></a>并<a data-i13n="cpos:10;pos:1" href="https://subscription.yahoo.net/Newsletter/Preference/sub?b=engadgetdeals&amp;src"><em>订阅 Engadget Deals 时事通讯，</em></a><em>了解最新的科技交易和购买建议。</em></p>本文最初发表在 Engadget 上：https://www.engadget.com/amazon-echo-show-5-is-back-on-sale-for-50-144458072.html?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/amazon-echo-show-5-is-back-on-sale-for-50-144458072.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> 95dd0912-7907-42e1-a693-dca0b063bb65</guid><dc:creator>杰夫·邓恩</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>恩杰特</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder>恩杰特</dc:rightsholder><pubDate>Fri, 14 Jul 2023 14:44:58 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1689346320</ingested><modified> 2023-07-14T14:52:11+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Technology & Electronics]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Jeff Dunn]]></category><media:content height="1080" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-07/44181410-2254-11ee-bfff-e556e8cf4b15" width="1800"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="1080" medium="image" url="https://media-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-07/44181410-2254-11ee-bfff-e556e8cf4b15" width="1800"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[Amazon]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[Amazon's Echo Show 5 smart display rests on a tablet in front of a rainy window.]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[Amazon Echo Show 5]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[The best smart home gadgets for 2023]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p>无论您是刚刚涉足智能家居领域，还是在不断扩大的设置中添加新设备，都有前所未有的物联网小工具可供您选择。但在您深入了解之前，我们有一些建议。其一，不要试图一次性装备整个智能家居——这对于新手和熟悉智能家居小工具的人来说都是如此。这不仅可能非常昂贵，而且我们认为通常最好先购买一两件物品，看看您是否喜欢它们，或者看看它们如何与您家庭生态系统的其他部分搭配。如果您还没有决定，您应该决定您喜欢哪个语音助手。我们在下面提供了一些关于如何选择合适设备的建议，以及我们对每个智能设备类别的最佳建议，以及适当的替代建议。</p><h2>开始之前，选择一个语音助手</h2><p>虽然许多最好的智能家居设备与平台无关，但有一些设备（尤其是智能扬声器和智能显示器）要求您选择语音助手。 Currently, that means deciding if you&#39;ll use the Google Assistant or Amazon&#39;s Alexa on a regular basis (I&#39;ll address Siri in a moment.) They&#39;re both compatible with various smart home products from light bulbs to robot vacuums, but there are certain devices that work best with either Google or Amazon. Nest products, for example, are more compatible and have more functionality with Google-powered speakers and displays. They can still work with Amazon devices, but certain features might be disabled. The same holds true with Amazon products: They work better if they&#39;re in the same ecosystem.</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><p> So how do you choose between Alexa and Google Assistant? It really depends on your personal preferences. Do you listen to Audible, watch Prime Video and tend to do a lot of shopping on Amazon? Then you might lean toward an Alexa-powered smart home device. Do you use a lot of Google services like YouTube and Google Podcasts? A Google-powered device might be best.</p><p> If you want a voice assistant that&#39;s great at answering questions, Google Assistant tends to be better than Alexa. Amazon&#39;s helper, on the other hand, currently supports more smart home products. The company&#39;s smart speakers and displays also support the Zigbee smart home protocol, and some devices even have built-in smart home hubs. Both Google and Amazon devices can sync with your calendar, though Google&#39;s tend to work better with Google services. Plus, if you already have an Android phone, you might be more comfortable with Google Assistant anyway.</p><p> But what about Siri? Apple&#39;s assistant supports voice commands as well, but it doesn&#39;t have as many compatible devices as Google or Amazon. The HomePod mini and the (now discontinued) HomePod are the only Siri-compatible speakers on the market at the moment, too. That said, it&#39;s not too hard to find Apple HomeKit-compatible gear as more third-party companies add support for it, but you currently have a smaller pool of devices to choose from.</p><h2> Best smart speaker: Sonos Era 100 </h2><p><core-commerce id="baa0cc8edc8945da8fbdcf8374e108dd" data-type="product-list"></core-commerce></p><p> Our recommendation for the best smart speaker is the <a data-i13n="elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Sonos;elmt:;cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=1e71dc69-0ad7-47e7-abf5-dc3926557fa3&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Sonos&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiIxZTcxZGM2OS0wYWQ3LTQ3ZTctYWJmNS1kYzM5MjY1NTdmYTMiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc29ub3MuY29tL2VuLXVzL3Nob3AvZXJhLTEwMCIsImNvbnRlbnRVdWlkIjoiODU5Y2U0MTgtZmU2Mi00YTRmLTk1NmYtMzAzYmU5ZTA1YTFmIn0&amp;signature=AQAAAdzzLNyIaAWtF5hlcu_AkSLL0HYMlTnGY7HwGt022nHY&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sonos.com%2Fen-us%2Fshop%2Fera-100" class="rapid-with-clickid">Sonos Era 100</a> . It&#39;s compact enough to fit in most areas in your home, but more importantly, it delivers excellent audio quality that&#39;s superior to a lot of other smart speakers out there. When tuned properly to the acoustics of your room — which requires the iOS app — the sound is fantastic, with punchy bass and clear highs. Unfortunately, the Android app doesn&#39;t have TruePlay tuning (Sonos has not said whether it&#39;s in the works), but the speakers should still sound admirable. It&#39;s also compatible with a slew of streaming services to play music, including major ones like Spotify and Pandora.</p><p> The main benefit that a Sonos speaker brings over the competition is that it&#39;s a gateway to a multi-room audio setup that you can build out over time. It&#39;s also convenient if you plan on building a home theater setup later on, as the Era 100 integrates well with Sonos soundbars.</p><h2> Runner-up: Amazon Echo Studio </h2><p><core-commerce id="1b76cce54193450bbefce2f537a538d0" data-type="product-list"></core-commerce></p><p> <a data-i13n="cpos:2;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAcrizQP0M3dw26ikW8a9J-cqOikD_fIqVampzaQ6QdwW&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FEcho-Studio%2Fdp%2FB07G9Y3ZMC">Amazon&#39;s Echo Studio</a> is a great choice if you know you prefer Alexa to the Google Assistant for voice control. The latest Studio, which was just announced, has been retooled with new spatial audio processing that improves on the company&#39;s previous 3D sound technology. It also has an improved frequency range, with increased mid-range clarity and deeper bass, and a built-in smart home hub for connecting things like smart lights, switches, plugs and more. And if you have a Fire TV device or an actual Fire TV set, you can pair the Studio with it to get a killer home-theater sound setup.</p><h2> Best $100 smart speaker: Amazon Echo </h2><p><core-commerce id="3c706840322642818fc81418444f5c4a" data-type="product-list"></core-commerce></p><p> For those with tighter budgets, there are a handful of smart speakers around $100. We <a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/2020-01-22-smart-speakers-guide-google-amazon-echo-sonos.html">recommend</a> picking up one of the three latest smart speakers from either Google, Amazon or Apple. Out of the three, we think the <a data-i13n="cpos:4;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiI2NmVhNTY3YS1jOTg3LTRjMmUtYTJmZi0wMjkwNGVmZGU2ZWEiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYW1hem9uLmNvbS9kcC9CMDdYS0Y1Uk0zP3RhZz1nZGd0MGMtcC1vLWduLTIwIiwiY29udGVudFV1aWQiOiI4NTljZTQxOC1mZTYyLTRhNGYtOTU2Zi0zMDNiZTllMDVhMWYifQ&amp;signature=AQAAAX9CbEyVHA8y3TYA0mphjqqwBYijwDeLvQA421LczJ7S&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2Fdp%2FB07XKF5RM3">Echo</a> has the best audio quality. Our colleague Nate Ingraham <a data-i13n="cpos:5;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/amazon-echo-2020-review-130046336.html">said</a> its bass is impressive and the mid-range frequencies are pretty powerful. You can also pair two together to get even better stereo sound.</p><p> That said, the <a data-i13n="cpos:6;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:B&amp;H Photo Video;elmt:" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=95276f3c-7b79-4c1e-803f-981cd9f7a968&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=B%26H+Photo+Video&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAASmZtA88P2g3MQRoBRqO644j9u3xVZrMLGthiEaLimjk&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bhphotovideo.com%2Fc%2Fproduct%2F1597174-REG%2Fgoogle_ga01586_us_nest_audio_charcoal.html">Nest Audio</a> and <a data-i13n="cpos:7;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:B&amp;H Photo Video;elmt:" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=95276f3c-7b79-4c1e-803f-981cd9f7a968&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=B%26H+Photo+Video&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAbQFlrompdgR0-n_Uq49c3hQSHpJFJl_enpYTvfuNlIR&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bhphotovideo.com%2Fc%2Fproduct%2F1598683-REG%2Fapple_aphomepmsg_homepod_mini_space_gray.html">HomePod mini</a> are no slouches either. The <a data-i13n="cpos:8;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/apple-homepod-mini-review-140030652.html">HomePod mini</a> sounds balanced, while the<a data-i13n="cpos:9;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/google-nest-audio-review-143012511.html">Nest Audio</a> has pretty good bass tones. Again, it all comes down to which assistant you prefer.</p><h2> Best Alexa smart display: Echo Show 8 </h2><p><core-commerce id="08eadfda4b5342bfb10627ce4b352c7f" data-type="product-list"></core-commerce></p><p> The best Alexa-powered smart display is the <a data-i13n="cpos:10;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-